<TITLE> BOA unveils logo of Indo-Bangladesh Bangla Games </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 29 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA) Tuesday unveiled the logo of the second Indo-Bangladesh Bangla Games with the slogan of 'sports for friendship'. BOA acting secretary general Kutubuddin Ahmed unveiled the logo at a programme at the National Sports Council. The Games for both Bangla athletes in nine disciplines is scheduled for Feb 22 to 26. The disciplines are football, cricket, athletic, swimming, shooting, volleyball, basketball, kabaddi and kho kho. The National Swimming Complex (swimming), the Suhrawardi Indoor Complex (basketball), Volleyball Stadium and Gazipur (volleyball), Outer Stadium Kabaddi Court (kabaddi), Kho Kho ground (kho kho), Army Stadium (Athletic), Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan (shooting), Bogra and Rajshahi (cricket), Narsingdi and Bangabandhu National Stadium (football) will host the events. "We have chosen the month of International Mother Language Day to hold the meet following the request of the West Bangla so that they can pay tributes to the martyrs of the historic language movement," said Kutubuddin. Kutubuddin hoped the home side would perform better this time, compared with the first edition meet in Kolkata last year as the players have been training for last three months. The BOA secretary general said that the Olympic Association of Asia has granted U$ 20,000 for the meet that would boost their financial position to complete the meet successfully. BOA joint secretary general Ashraf Uddin Ahmed Chunnu has been appointed chef de mission of the Bangladesh contingent while BOA member Anisur Rahman Dipu will act as general manager of the team. BOA high-ups, representatives of nine disciplines and chairmen or co-chairmen of the different committees for the meet were present on the occasion. 
